      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":48},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":52},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":58}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":2,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":60,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start very relaxed, let the body settle into rhythm.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Conversational effort throughout — if you need to slow down, slow down.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Walk or easy jog to finish.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes very easy jogging or brisk walking before settling into run pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"5 minutes easy walking or light stretching post-run.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run is purely aerobic — keep effort genuinely easy. The goal is blood flow and gentle stimulus, not fitness building. If legs still feel flat, keep to the lower end of the easy zone.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"title\":\"Reduced Tempo Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":48,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":280,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Gentle warm-up jog — let your legs find their rhythm before any quality work.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":28,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":280,\"intensity\":\"Threshold\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Comfortably hard, threshold effort — you should be able to speak in short phrases. If pace feels unattainable today, back off to 290-295 s/km and note how it feels.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog cooldown to flush the legs.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"10 minutes easy running before the tempo segment begins.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"10 minutes easy jogging followed by light leg swings and calf stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Volume is trimmed from 12 km to 10 km and the quality segment is shortened to give your body a chance to respond well to threshold work again. Use this as a confidence reset rather than a test — a solid 28 minutes at threshold pace is a meaningful workout.\",\"perceived_effort\":6},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"Interval\",\"title\":\"Short Interval Session — Reset\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":55,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":250,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":12,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Thorough warm-up including strides at the end if legs feel ready.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":20,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":250,\"intensity\":\"VO2Max\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"4 reps instead of 6 — quality over quantity. Stop a rep early if form breaks down; that is the right call, not a failure.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Recovery\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":4,\"notes\":\"Full recovery between reps — walk or very easy jog until breathing is comfortable.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":10,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy jog to close out the session.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"12 minutes easy running, finishing with 2-3 light strides if legs feel responsive.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"10 minutes easy jogging and light stretching — focus on hip flexors and calves.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Reduced to 4 reps to match what your body is ready to execute well right now. The goal is to finish all four feeling like you could have done one more — that signals you are on the right side of the effort curve heading into next week.\",\"perceived_effort\":7},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Moderate Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":18,\"target_duration_minutes\":107,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":355,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":355,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":7,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":365,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start slower than feels necessary — long runs are all about the finish, not the start.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":93,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":355,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady aerobic effort throughout. No surges, no racing — this is a time-on-feet investment.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":7,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":365,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease off the pace in the final few minutes and walk the last 2-3 minutes.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"First 7 minutes deliberately slower than easy pace — resist the urge to find rhythm too quickly.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk 2-3 minutes after finishing and do light standing stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Pulled back from 22 km to 18 km to rebuild long run confidence at an achievable distance. Running 18 km well is worth far more than struggling through 22 km right now. The distance will come back quickly once the body is responding well again.\",\"perceived_effort\":6}],\"forward_path\":\"Week 2 target steps up to 52 km — roughly an 8% lift from this week's adjusted 48 km — with the long run returning to 20 km and the interval session back to 5 reps. If that week goes well and the quality sessions feel controlled, Week 3 moves to 58 km with 6 reps and the long run at 21-22 km, bringing you back onto the original progression curve before Week 4. The sub-3:15 goal is fully intact — a brief consolidation week now protects the fitness you have already built and sets up stronger quality sessions across the remaining 23 weeks.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-10,\"rationale\":\"Three sessions in a row where the body just wasn't firing at full capacity — that tells a clear and consistent story, and shutting down the interval session early on Saturday was exactly the right call. The pattern in your logs points to accumulated fatigue that hasn't fully cleared, likely building from the opening days of the new meso cycle. What you're feeling in your legs is real, and working through it at prescribed load would dig the hole deeper rather than fill it. Here's what I've adjusted: this week's total volume comes down from 58 km to 48 km, with the long run trimmed to 18 km, the interval session reduced to 4 reps, and the tempo shortened slightly. Each session is still meaningful — just calibrated to what your body can absorb well right now rather than what the original schedule demanded. Looking ahead, Week 2 steps back up to 52 km and Week 3 to 58 km, which keeps the path to your sub-3:15 goal clear. One consolidation week now means the quality sessions over the next two months will actually land — and that's where the real fitness gains happen.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
